{"content":[{"abbv":"wlc","answer":"The sins of equals are, besides the neglect of the duties required, the undervaluing of the worth, envying the gifts, grieving at the advancement of prosperity one of another; and usurping preeminence one over another.","citation":"WLC 132","long_citation":"Larger Catechism 132","name":"Larger Catechism","number":"132","prooftexts":{},"question":"What are the sins of equals?","section_title":"","type":"catechism"}],"content_with_prooftexts":[{"abbv":"wlc","answer":"The sins of equals are, besides the neglect of the duties required,<sup id='fnref:wlc1'><a href='#fn:wlc1' rel='footnote' style='text-decoration: none;'>1</a></sup> the undervaluing of the worth,<sup id='fnref:wlc2'><a href='#fn:wlc2' rel='footnote' style='text-decoration: none;'>2</a></sup> envying the gifts,<sup id='fnref:wlc3'><a href='#fn:wlc3' rel='footnote' style='text-decoration: none;'>3</a></sup> grieving at the advancement of prosperity one of another;<sup id='fnref:wlc4'><a href='#fn:wlc4' rel='footnote' style='text-decoration: none;'>4</a></sup> and usurping preeminence one over another.<sup id='fnref:wlc5'><a href='#fn:wlc5' rel='footnote' style='text-decoration: none;'>5</a></sup>","citation":"WLC 132","long_citation":"Larger Catechism 132","name":"Larger Catechism","number":"132","prooftexts":{"1":"<div class=\"esv\"><h5>Romans 13:8</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\">\n<p id=\"p45013008.06-1\">Owe no one anything, except to love each other, for the one who loves another has fulfilled the law.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>","2":"<div class=\"esv\"><h5>2 Timothy 3:3</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><p id=\"p55003003.01-1\">heartless, unappeasable, slanderous, without self-control, brutal, not loving good,</p>\n</div><h5>Proverbs 14:21</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><div class=\"block-indent\">\n<p class=\"line-group\" id=\"p20014021.01-2\">Whoever despises his neighbor is a sinner,<br />\n<span class=\"indent\"></span>but blessed is he who is generous to the poor.</p>\n</div>\n</div><h5>Isaiah 65:5</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><div class=\"block-indent\">\n<p class=\"line-group\" id=\"p23065005.01-3\">who say, &#8220;Keep to yourself,<br />\n<span class=\"indent\"></span>do not come near me, for I am too holy for you.&#8221;<br />\nThese are a smoke in my nostrils,<br />\n<span class=\"indent\"></span>a fire that burns all the day.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","3":"<div class=\"esv\"><h5>Acts 7:9</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><p id=\"p44007009.01-1\">&#8220;And the patriarchs, jealous of Joseph, sold him into Egypt; but God was with him</p>\n</div><h5>Galatians 5:26</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><p id=\"p48005026.01-2\">Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, envying one another.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>","4":"<div class=\"esv\"><h5>Numbers 12:2</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><p id=\"p04012002.01-1\">And they said, &#8220;Has the <span class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> indeed spoken only through Moses? Has he not spoken through us also?&#8221; And the <span class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard it.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>","5":"<div class=\"esv\"><h5>3 John 1:9</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\"><p id=\"p64001009.01-1\">I have written something to the church, but Diotrephes, who likes to put himself first, does not acknowledge our authority.</p>\n</div><h5>Luke 22:24</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\">\n<p id=\"p42022024.05-2\">A dispute also arose among them, as to which of them was to be regarded as the greatest.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>"},"question":"What are the sins of equals?","section_title":"","type":"catechism"}],"feed":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<title></title>\n\n</head>\n<body>\n<h5 class=\"header mb-1\" style=\"display:block; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:18px\">Larger Catechism</h5>\n<p class=\"question mb-0\" style=\"display:block; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:16px\"><span class=\"q\">Q <em>132.</em></span>\nWhat are the sins of equals?</p>\n<div class=\"answer\" style=\"display:block; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:16px\"><p style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\"><span class=\"q\">A.  </span> The sins of equals are, besides the neglect of the duties required,<sup id=\"fnref:wlc1\"><a href=\"#fn:wlc1\" rel=\"footnote\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">1</a></sup> the undervaluing of the worth,<sup id=\"fnref:wlc2\"><a href=\"#fn:wlc2\" rel=\"footnote\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">2</a></sup> envying the gifts,<sup id=\"fnref:wlc3\"><a href=\"#fn:wlc3\" rel=\"footnote\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">3</a></sup> grieving at the advancement of prosperity one of another;<sup id=\"fnref:wlc4\"><a href=\"#fn:wlc4\" rel=\"footnote\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">4</a></sup> and usurping preeminence one over another.<sup id=\"fnref:wlc5\"><a href=\"#fn:wlc5\" rel=\"footnote\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">5</a></sup></p></div>\n\n    <div class=\"prooftexts\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">\n        <ol class=\"disc\">\n        \n            <li class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn:1\">\n                <div class=\"esv\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Romans 13:8</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p45013008.06-1\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">Owe no one anything, except to love each other, for the one who loves another has fulfilled the law.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n            </li>\n        \n            <li class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn:2\">\n                <div class=\"esv\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">2 Timothy 3:3</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p55003003.01-1\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">heartless, unappeasable, slanderous, without self-control, brutal, not loving good,</p>\n</div>\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Proverbs 14:21</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<div class=\"block-indent\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p class=\"line-group\" id=\"p20014021.01-2\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">Whoever despises his neighbor is a sinner,\n<span class=\"indent\"></span>but blessed is he who is generous to the poor.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Isaiah 65:5</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<div class=\"block-indent\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p class=\"line-group\" id=\"p23065005.01-3\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">who say, \u201cKeep to yourself,\n<span class=\"indent\"></span>do not come near me, for I am too holy for you.\u201d\nThese are a smoke in my nostrils,\n<span class=\"indent\"></span>a fire that burns all the day.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n            </li>\n        \n            <li class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn:3\">\n                <div class=\"esv\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Acts 7:9</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p44007009.01-1\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\u201cAnd the patriarchs, jealous of Joseph, sold him into Egypt; but God was with him</p>\n</div>\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Galatians 5:26</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p48005026.01-2\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, envying one another.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n            </li>\n        \n            <li class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn:4\">\n                <div class=\"esv\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Numbers 12:2</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p04012002.01-1\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">And they said, \u201cHas the <span class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> indeed spoken only through Moses? Has he not spoken through us also?\u201d And the <span class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard it.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n            </li>\n        \n            <li class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn:5\">\n                <div class=\"esv\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">3 John 1:9</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p64001009.01-1\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">I have written something to the church, but Diotrephes, who likes to put himself first, does not acknowledge our authority.</p>\n</div>\n<h5 style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0; font-size:14px\">Luke 22:24</h5>\n<div class=\"esv-text\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">\n<p id=\"p42022024.05-2\" style=\"display:inline; font-family:Georgia, Serif; margin:0; padding:0\">A dispute also arose among them, as to which of them was to be regarded as the greatest.  (<a href=\"http://www.esv.org\" class=\"copyright\">ESV</a>)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n            </li>\n        \n        </ol>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"What are the sins of equals?"}
